03 Data Analysis

Designed for Shantel

Harry Lu, dl947@cornell.edu

HOME

1 Goal

  • Know the workflow of data analysis
    • EDA
    • Use built-in functions/customized algorithms to find the answer on a small scale dataset
    • Scale the small analysis up to a large dataset
    • Automate/Semi-automate the work if needed
    • Present findings, generate reports, make recommendations to clients or stakeholders

2 Public Dataset

  • Built-in dataset
  • How to find: Google search “public dataset”
  • Examples:
    • Free Public Data Sets For Analysis | Tableau
    • Find Open Datasets and Machine Learning Projects | Kaggle
    • More…

2.1 Iris

  • Source: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Iris
  • Download: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/iris/
    • bezdekIris.data or iris.data
    • iris.names

2.2 Wine

  • Source: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Wine
  • Download: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/wine/
    • wine.data
    • wine.names

2.3 Wine Quality

  • Source: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Wine+Quality
  • Download: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/wine-quality/
    • winequality-red.csv
    • winequality-white.csv
    • winequality.names

3 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

  1. Read dataset documentation, understand the background behind the data
  2. Clean dataset
  3. Summarize columns, understand the data
